You played an accurate transcription of Villanova Junction, thank you :-))))

The piece is in A minor scale (5th fret), and easy to play once you get used to
play the octave riffs.

For the main octave riff, I always use my thumb for the lower strings of the
first 4 notes and play 5th note and octave slides with my index finger
and pinky:


[tab]e|--------------------------|
B|-----------8--------------|
G|------5-7----7/9\7\5-7----|
D|-7-7-------5-----------7--|
A|------3-5----5/7\5\3-5----|
E|-5-5-------------------5--|
   T T  T T              T[/tab]

I fret 6th and 5th string like so, but you'll find the most comfortable fingering
position for yourself after a few runs through the song. This is just the fingering
I use. Furthermore, fret 6th (low E) string with your thumb throughout the entire
song.

You can improvise on minor scales yourself and stretch the song to 5-10 minutes.


************************************

| ^           Hammer on or Pull off
| hb          1/2 step bend
| wb          1 step bend
| br          bend and release
| bp          pre-bend
| /           Slide up
| \           Slide down
| ~~~         Finger vibrato
| tr''        trill until dots disappear
| trem pick   tremolo pick


************************************